Sprint 0: Experimenting with representation

Mike Johnson

2021-02-24

Problem/Background

Three tenets of hy_features are:

  • a catchment realization must be able to perform the functions of a flowpath and a catchment area.
  • to support multiple scale models and data, any catchment realization may be composed of a network of other catchment realizations.
  • Catchment and nexus provide identity and topology. They do not have attributes or geometry.

Thus, we need geometry to inform processing, and we need that geometry to associate flow paths and catchment but be used intercahangbly.

We have 2 distinct files with a shared ID (comid):

source('../R/prep_flownetwork.R')

og_cat <- read_sf("../data/huc1805000502-catchment.gpkg") %>% 
   dplyr::select(comid = FEATUREID)

og_fl = read_sf("../data/huc1805000502-flowlines.gpkg") %>% 
  prep_flownetwork(og_cat)

Lets create a single object that contains both “realizations” is a single go:

source("../R/toy_functions.R")

hy = make_hy(og_fl, og_cat)

Looking at the header of the print, we see that the ‘active’ geometry column is called cat_geom. Thus, if we plot, we get:

plot(st_geometry(hy))

But, often we want/need the flowpath represneation! So lets “activate” the flow path:

hy = activate(hy, "fl")

Flow path should be LINESTRINGS, not MULTILINESTRINGS. Always!

hy = multi_to_line(activate(hy, "fl"))
